1
00:00:17,090 --> 00:00:19,660
This won't ever reach you.

2
00:00:20,950 --> 00:00:24,570
This feeling is neither admiration nor nostalgia.

3
00:00:24,570 --> 00:00:26,550
This pain is...

4
00:00:30,200 --> 00:00:31,840
Ohara,

5
00:00:32,590 --> 00:00:34,240
I like you.

6
00:00:36,940 --> 00:00:38,460
Crap!

7
00:00:40,670 --> 00:00:44,620
You're always the first thing my eyes are drawn to.

8
00:00:48,020 --> 00:00:50,450
And each time, I...

9
00:00:52,420 --> 00:00:56,930
So Fujiwara, the idol of 2nd year, also wants Ohara?

10
00:00:56,930 --> 00:00:59,720
Of course she does. This is Ohara we're talking about.

11
00:00:59,720 --> 00:01:01,590
I didn't even make a move on her,

12
00:01:01,590 --> 00:01:04,430
- and I feel heartbroken.
- Poor you.

13
00:01:04,430 --> 00:01:08,610
Hey! You guys agreed that Fujiwara was cute!

14
00:01:08,610 --> 00:01:10,800
Sure, 'cause you insisted.

15
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:11,920
Dude...

16
00:01:11,920 --> 00:01:16,010
I guess girls just like that cool personality of his.

17
00:01:16,010 --> 00:01:18,910
No way! Cool? More like straight cold.

18
00:01:18,910 --> 00:01:22,370
Either way, romance seems like it'd be a cinch for him.

19
00:01:22,370 --> 00:01:24,400
What are you guys doing out here?

20
00:01:28,810 --> 00:01:30,900
- Adolescent puppy love?
- Who says that?

21
00:01:30,900 --> 00:01:35,100
Well, here's a taste of adolescence for you too, Ashiya.

22
00:01:35,100 --> 00:01:38,100
Test-takers who scored under a 40 get afterschool remedial.

23
00:01:38,100 --> 00:01:40,230
So, Ashiya.

24
00:01:40,230 --> 00:01:42,070
What'd you score?

25
00:01:43,490 --> 00:01:44,720
Not telling.

26
00:01:44,720 --> 00:01:45,910
[28 points]

27
00:01:45,910 --> 00:01:48,390
28 points...

28
00:01:48,390 --> 00:01:52,120
Please, don't say it out loud!

29
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:55,930
And just to satiate my curiosity, what'd you score?

30
00:01:55,930 --> 00:01:57,830
98.

31
00:01:59,950 --> 00:02:02,790
How did childhood friends like us,

32
00:02:02,790 --> 00:02:05,710
end up as complete opposites of each other?

33
00:02:05,710 --> 00:02:09,660
- I'm so done for...
- For now,

34
00:02:09,660 --> 00:02:11,480
let's take this worksheet from the top.

35
00:02:14,290 --> 00:02:16,690
For this question...

36
00:02:16,690 --> 00:02:22,180
We use this formula to calculate the value of cosine.

37
00:02:22,180 --> 00:02:24,510
I think I got it!

38
00:02:24,510 --> 00:02:29,130
Yamato, I swear my brain only understands your way of explaining things.

39
00:02:29,130 --> 00:02:31,030
I wonder why?

40
00:02:31,030 --> 00:02:33,240
Because we're childhood friends?

41
00:02:33,240 --> 00:02:35,480
I seriously doubt it.

42
00:02:36,570 --> 00:02:42,440
But I can't deny the fact that I'd be useless without you.

43
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:48,720
Watch this split... huh?

44
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:52,720
I broke it!

45
00:02:52,720 --> 00:02:54,840
That always happens with those.

46
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:56,840
I guess so.

47
00:02:58,140 --> 00:03:00,600
Anyways, thanks for tutoring me. Here.

48
00:03:01,410 --> 00:03:04,920
- It's fine, I'll take the shorter half.
- But...

49
00:03:06,630 --> 00:03:08,040
Wait, let's do this!

50
00:03:08,040 --> 00:03:10,750
- Just take a bite out of this.
- Huh?

51
00:03:10,750 --> 00:03:12,990
For the even split.

52
00:03:13,670 --> 00:03:15,450
Nah, it's all right.

53
00:03:15,450 --> 00:03:17,730
Hurry, it's already melting.

54
00:03:17,730 --> 00:03:19,050
Open wide.

55
00:03:27,010 --> 00:03:29,410
And with that, it's perfect halfsies.

56
00:03:41,140 --> 00:03:45,040
So, what's the deal with you and Fujiwara?

57
00:03:45,040 --> 00:03:46,650
Are you two going out?

58
00:03:46,650 --> 00:03:48,340
No.

59
00:03:48,340 --> 00:03:52,200
Aw, what a missed opportunity! She's so cute.

60
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:55,810
It doesn't matter if I don't like her myself.

61
00:03:55,810 --> 00:03:57,380
If you say so.

62
00:03:58,910 --> 00:04:03,390
I wonder how much longer we'll be able to do this stuff after school.

63
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:06,990
I mean, if you get yourself a girlfriend,

64
00:04:06,990 --> 00:04:09,890
you're definitely not staying to tutor me.

65
00:04:09,890 --> 00:04:12,570
That doesn't just apply to me.

66
00:04:12,570 --> 00:04:14,750
You could be the one to get a girlfriend first.

67
00:04:14,750 --> 00:04:16,830
Me, a girlfriend? No way.

68
00:04:16,830 --> 00:04:19,480
I'm not popular like you.

69
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:21,550
I'm not even smart!

70
00:04:21,550 --> 00:04:22,890
I'm not popular.

71
00:04:22,890 --> 00:04:25,320
You are!

72
00:04:26,350 --> 00:04:30,370
So, does Mr. Popular have a crush on anyone?

73
00:04:37,540 --> 00:04:39,250
Kakeru.

74
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:41,370
Huh?

75
00:04:45,250 --> 00:04:47,010
Kakeru.

76
00:04:47,940 --> 00:04:50,170
Oh, oh...

77
00:04:59,670 --> 00:05:01,580
Ashiya!

78
00:05:01,580 --> 00:05:04,330
If you've got the brains, use them in the first place!

79
00:05:04,330 --> 00:05:08,680
That's what you were talking about? I was so nervous!

80
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:12,390
I need to stop by the bookstore, so I'll be heading out.

81
00:05:12,390 --> 00:05:14,050
- Really?
- Goodbye.

82
00:05:14,050 --> 00:05:15,810
Yeah.

83
00:05:15,810 --> 00:05:17,710
Take care.

84
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:48,170
[I Cannot Reach You]

85
00:05:48,870 --> 00:05:50,530
Morning.
[Episode 1]

86
00:05:50,530 --> 00:05:52,790
We have PE today.

87
00:05:52,790 --> 00:05:54,720
What a pain!

88
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:56,950
And it's your favorite, basketball.

89
00:05:56,950 --> 00:05:59,030
- Shut it.
- Look, it's Ohara!

90
00:05:59,030 --> 00:06:01,130
We're so lucky to catch a glimpse of him.

91
00:06:01,130 --> 00:06:03,530
Today's gonna be a good day!

92
00:06:03,530 --> 00:06:06,530
Man, you've turned into an omen of good luck.

93
00:06:06,530 --> 00:06:10,840
Big news, Ashiya. Fujino got himself a girlfriend!

94
00:06:10,840 --> 00:06:13,060
